title: Woody Guthrie - Columbia River Collection (MP3@VBR) [FrankFoo]
description:
Woody Guthrie - Columbia River Collection

Info:
In 1941, Woody age 28, was hired by the Bonneville Power Administration in Portland, Oregon to write music for a film about the Columbia River and public power. 
This collection presents all known recordings of Woody singing his Columbia River songs, including recordings lost 40 years ago. Among the classic songs are Roll On Columbia, The Biggest Thing That Man Has Done, and Grand Coulee Dam, for a total of 17 songs. 

Included: NFO, PLS, M3U
